Sentencas: Deposits of La1-xSrxMnO3+/-delta used as cathode materials in solid oxide fuel cells are obtained by oxidation of nitrate precursors in a low pressure RF plasma reactor equipped with a convergent nozzle.
Titulo: Effects of plasma parameters on the properties of La1-xSrxMnO3 thin layers deposited in low-pressure RF plasma wave shock reactor

Sentencas: Impedance measurements showed the role of plasma parameters on the electrical conductivity of deposits.
Titulo: Effects of plasma parameters on the properties of La1-xSrxMnO3 thin layers deposited in low-pressure RF plasma wave shock reactor

Sentencas: Infrared analysis of deposits permitted to measure the role of plasma parameters on the conversion rate of nitrate precursors.
Titulo: Effects of plasma parameters on the properties of La1-xSrxMnO3 thin layers deposited in low-pressure RF plasma wave shock reactor

Sentencas: Oxygen and hydroxyl radicals produced by plasma are found to be the major reactive species that lead to the oxidation of nitrate precursors in this process.
Titulo: Effects of plasma parameters on the properties of La1-xSrxMnO3 thin layers deposited in low-pressure RF plasma wave shock reactor
